Corrected for background using the black resonance
technique, using samples of manganese, aluminum and
SiO2. All points between 2.38 keV (Mn) and 440 keV (O)
were fitted by a simple power law in flight time and
extrapolated to 1 MeV. The fraction of time-dependent
background varied from 0.002 at 2.38keV to 0.28 at
440 keV, and was taken as 0.02 at 1 MeV.
